snippet.textDisplay: Well...beyond all the rivalries over land, people, cricket and everything else, here we have the moving human stories of love and break up expressed through music, which we have shared perpetually without a strand of difference or conflict. This song leaves me stoked every time and reminds me that we all belong to each other. Much love to Coke Studio Pakistan crew, all the instrumentalists, back-up singers and Momina and Asim. And the people of Pakistan to encourage such a lovely platform for independent artists. A big hug from India. :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Baatien teri karte hue thak ke so jati hun, sirhane aasman, 
jaane kahan mud jati he dekhte dekhte tujhe yeh galiyan
teri tarah khusboo chale, taare humhari tarah raato se mile, 

Suni nahi zamane ne teri meri kahaaniyaan, karde koi nawazishein karam mehrbaniyan, 
yeh aarzoo thi ke dekhe zamanaa, hum jaisa koi deewana nahi, 
kar de koi nawazishein karam mehrbaniyan, 

Raat andheri mechut rahe the, tum ek savera dhund rahe the, 
sadiyon se jaise jaag rahe the, pyaar ko apne thanp rahe the, 
phir ghir pade, koi mila na sahara kya kare, 
suni nahi zamane ne teri meri kahaaniyaan, 

Tera wo pyaar yaad aaega, 
bhulega na yeh dil mera, 
kya ho gya socha na tha, 
tera wo pyaar, tera wo pyaar 
tera wo pyaar, tera wo pyaar, 

Teri wo khamoshiyan keh deti thi wo sabhi, jo tu na keh saki, 
kaise batati tujhe, sharmati thi me, 
jaise aanchal me jalta diya, 
Khoye kaha mujhko bata! 
tera wo pyaar yaad aaega, 
bhulega na yeh dil mera - 2
kya ho gaya socha na tha.. ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤😍😍😍😍
